Polish Stocks: Bogdanka, KGHM Polska Miedz Move on Warsaw Bourse

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 
2011-10-13T13:12:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/polish-stocks-bogdanka-kghm-polska-miedz-move-on-warsaw-bourse.html
Poland ’s WIG20 Index fell 26.10, or
1.1 percent, to 2,290.55 at 2:45 p.m. in Warsaw, heading for the
steepest daily drop in more than a week.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
Warsaw Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Lubelski Wegiel Bogdanka SA (LWB PW), Poland’s second-
largest publicly traded coal producer, declined 1.1 percent to
104.3 zloty. Thermal coal for 2012 delivery to Amsterdam,
Rotterdam or Antwerp decreased as much as 1.9 percent to $118.50
a metric ton, its lowest level since Oct. 5, and last traded at
$118.75, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)  , the copper producer with the
biggest European mine output, declined 1.8 percent to 146.3
zloty, heading for the biggest one-day drop in a week. Copper
fell in  New York  on concern Europe’s lingering sovereign-debt
crisis may hamper economies in Asian countries such as China,
the top global consumer of the metal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pawel Kozlowski in Warsaw 
